      • getActionData

        default ByteBuffer getActionData()
        Retrieves the action data as a ByteBuffer view of the underlying structure data. This data consists of a series of AssistFieldStruct structures.
        Returns:
        a ByteBuffer constrained to the action data

      • getAssistFields

        default List<AssistFieldStruct> getAssistFields()
        Retrieves the action data as a list of AssistFieldStruct objects. These objects are views onto the underlying data, though the association will be broken if they are resized.
        Returns:
        a List of AssistFieldStruct objects

      • setActionData

        default CDActionByForm setActionData(byte[] actionData)
        Sets the action data for this record.

        Note: when modifying this data manually, it is important to also call setFieldCount(int) to reflect the number of AssistFieldStruct structures present.

        Parameters:
        actionData - the new action data to set
        Returns:
        this record
